snippet: Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce edged Carmelita Jeter of the United States and won the women’s 100 meters with a time of 10.75 seconds
abstract: Jamaican sprinter Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce edges American Carmelita Jeter to win gold in the women’s 100 meters; Jamaica's Veronica Campbell-Brown takes bronze; Mo Farah of Great Britain wins the men's 10,000 meters and American Galen Rump earns the silver.

byline.original: By KEN BELSON and MARY PILON

lead_paragraph: Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce edged Carmelita Jeter of the United States and won the women’s 100 meters with a time of 10.75 seconds

headline.seo: Jamaican Fraser-Pryce Successfully Defends Gold in Women’s 100
headline.main: Round One in Sprints to Jamaica; Briton Takes 10,000
